1 G. The conduct of allopathic physicians and physician
2 assistants pursuant to this act shall be regulated by the State
3 Board of Medical Licensure and Supervision. The conduct of
4 osteopathic physicians pursuant to this act shall be regulated by
5 the State Board of Osteopathic Examiners. The conduct of Registered
6 Nurses, Licensed Practical Nurses, and Advanced Practice Registered
7 Nurses pursuant to this act shall be regulated by the Oklahoma Board
8 of Nursing.
9 H. G. Nothing in this act shall prohibit any person in the
10 healing arts, in this state, under any other act, from engaging in
11 the practice for which he or she is duly licensed.
12 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
13 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
14 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
15 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
